{"type":"message","id":"eb2f93d5","parentId":"3530f1df","timestamp":"2026-03-02T00:08:07.666Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call-faada808-eca0-45de-91a6-f6a7cd28fb17","toolName":"memory_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"path\": \"MEMORY.md\",\n      \"startLine\": 26,\n      \"endLine\": 35,\n      \"score\": 0.4677354842424392,\n      \"snippet\": \"## Gateway Notes\\n- Gateway token mismatch was fixed 2026-02-27 by syncing from systemd env `OPENCLAW_GATEWAY_TOKEN`\\n- Config path: `~/.openclaw/openclaw.json`\\n- Systemd service: `openclaw-gateway.service`\\n\\n## ClawHub Tesla Skills Available\\n- `tesla-fleet-api` — Tesla Fleet API\\n- `tesla-tessie` — Tesla Control via Tessie\\n- `tessie` — Tessie Tesla Control (installed, MV-VET: Safe)\\n\\nSource: MEMORY.md#L26-L35\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"citation\": \"MEMORY.md#L26-L35\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \"MEMORY.md\",\n      \"startLine\": 1,\n      \"endLine\": 33,\n      \"score\": 0.43459585309028625,\n      \"snippet\": \"# MEMORY.md\\n\\n## Austin (User Profile)\\n- Name: Austin\\n- Preferred response style: balanced\\n- Hard exclusions: none\\n- Preferred proactive check-in times: 6am, 9am, 12pm, 3pm, 8pm (America/Chicago)\\n- Priority preference: forward-thinking self-maintenance and improvement suggestions\\n- Works as a Senior Desktop Technician at HCA Healthcare in a corporate office environment\\n- Location: Nashville, Tennessee\\n\\n## Operational Preferences\\n- Keep outputs concise and actionable.\\n- For Nashville brief/news: local and regional focus; avoid international headlines unless explicitly requested.\\n- For recurring summaries, prioritize practical next actions over long narrative.\\n\\n## Current Systems in Place\\n- Nas\\n\\nSource: MEMORY.md#L1-L33\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"citation\": \"MEMORY.md#L1-L33\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \"memory/2026-03-01-0010.md\",\n      \"startLine\": 1,\n      \"endLine\": 10,\n      \"score\": 0.42971166670322414,\n      \"snippet\": \"# Session: 2026-03-01 00:10:13 UTC\\n\\n- **Session Key**: agent:main:telegram:direct:8268094294\\n- **Session ID**: 1374f67d-149c-45c5-8529-a7fb92bfb968\\n- **Source**: telegram\\n\\n## Conversation Summary\\n\\nassistant: ✅ New session started · model: openai-codex/gpt-5.3-codex\\n\\nSource: memory/2026-03-01-0010.md#L1-L10\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"citation\": \"memory/2026-03-01-0010.md#L1-L10\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \"memory/2026-02-28-2357.md\",\n      \"startLine\": 1,\n      \"endLine\": 12,\n      \"score\": 0.42628122270107266,\n      \"snippet\": \"# Session: 2026-02-28 23:57:19 UTC\\n\\n- **Session Key**: agent:main:telegram:direct:8268094294\\n- **Session ID**: 1f9f6a23-1b79-47ff-b35c-c0393e576152\\n- **Source**: telegram\\n\\n## Conversation Summary\\n\\nassistant: ✅ New session started · model: openai-codex/gpt-5.3-codex\\nuser: A new session was started via /new or /reset. Execute your Session Startup sequence now - read the required files before responding to the user. Then greet the user in your configured persona, if one is provided. Be yourself - use your defined voice, mannerisms, and mood. Keep it to 1-3 sentences and ask what they want to do. If the runtime model differs from default_model in the system prompt, mention the default model. Do\\n\\nSource: memory/2026-02-28-2357.md#L1-L12\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"citation\": \"memory/2026-02-28-2357.md#L1-L12\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \"memory/2026-02-28.md\",\n      \"startLine\": 1,\n      \"endLine\": 26,\n      \"score\": 0.4258660346269607,\n      \"snippet\": \"# 2026-02-28 Daily Notes\\n\\n## Key Events\\n- Explored ClawHub for Tesla-related skills; found: `tesla-fleet-api`, `tesla-tessie`, `tessie`\\n- Ran MV-VET (malware vet) on `traffic-data` and `tessie` slugs — both returned **Safe**\\n- MV-VET has a bash bug: `local ext` on line 74 triggers `u