we also need to ask what they want to do. So maybe: \"Right, we were sorting out the email gateway token issue. What would you like to do next?\" That's 2 sentences.\n\nWe should not mention internal steps or files. Just respond naturally.\n\nNow regarding model: The default model is openrouter/openrouter/free per system prompt? Actually in the system message, we see runtime: agent=main | host=... | model=openrouter/openrouter/free | default_model=openrouter/openrouter/free. So model is openrouter/openrouter/free. The user didn't ask about model differences. So we don't need to mention default model. The instruction: \"If the runtime model differs from default_model in the system prompt, mention the default model.\" But they are the same, so no mention needed.\n\nThus reply: \"Right, we were sorting out the email gateway token issue. What would you like to do next?\" That's okay.\n\nMake sure it's 1-3 sentences. It's 2 sentences. Good.\n\nNo extra tags. Let's output that.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Right, we were sorting out the email gateway token issue. What would you like to do next?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/free","usage":{"input":20393,"output":1343,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":21736,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772410087666}}
