{"type":"message","id":"e18a963a","parentId":"61a4e15f","timestamp":"2026-03-02T00:10:45.575Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"chatcmpl-tool-1436ff","toolName":"memory_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"path\": \"memory/2026-03-01-1827.md\",\n      \"startLine\": 676,\n      \"endLine\": 709,\n      \"score\": 0.8035296112298964,\n      \"snippet\": \"endpoint = \\\"https://gateway.maton.ai/google-mail/v1/send\\\"  # update if needed\\npayload = {\\n  \\\"from\\\": \\\"OpenCopilot Digest <austin.king@parallon.com>\\\",\\n  \\\"to\\\": \\\"austin.king@parallon.com\\\",\\n  \\\"subject\\\": \\\"MATON test email\\\",\\n  \\\"text\\\": \\\"Hello – this is a test from OpenCopilot.\\\"\\n}\\nheaders = {\\\"Authorization\\\": f\\\"Bearer {key}\\\"} if key else {}\\nprint(\\\"Key present:\\\", bool(key))\\nresp = requests.post(endpoint, headers=headers, data=payload, timeout=15)\\nprint(\\\"HTTP status:\\\", resp.status_code)\\ntry:\\n  print(\\\"Response JSON:\\\", resp.json())\\nexcept Exception:\\n  print(\\\"Raw response:\\\", resp.text[:400])\\nPY\\n- What to look for:\\n  - 200/201 with a useful JSON -> API is reachable and key okay.\\n  - 401/403 -> key or scope\\n\\nSource: memory/2026-03-01-1827.md#L676-L709\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"citation\": \"memory/2026-03-01-1827.md#L676-L709\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \"memory/2026-03-01-1827.md\",\n      \"startLine\": 539,\n      \"endLine\": 582,\n      \"score\": 0.7950693875551224,\n      \"snippet\": \"- The script might have **exited silently** (e.g., `SystemExit` with no print statements) if a required variable was missing.\\n\\n### What we need to confirm\\n1. **`MATON_API_KEY` is actually set** in the environment where the script runs.\\n2. **The endpoint URL is correct** (the placeholder may need to be replaced with the real MATON Gmail API endpoint you have access to).\\n3. **The request payload format** (field names, `from`, `to`, `subject`, `text`, `file`) matches what the MATON API expects.\\n\\n### Immediate troubleshooting steps (run them in the same shell)\\n\\n```bash\\n# 1️⃣ Verify the API key is present\\necho \\\"MATON_API_KEY → ${MATON_API_KEY:-<MISSING>}\\\"\\n\\n# 2️⃣ Verify the sender email (used in t\\n\\nSource: memory/2026-03-01-1827.md#L539-L582\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"citation\": \"memory/2026-03-01-1827.md#L539-L582\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \"memory/2026-03-01-1827.md\",\n      \"startLine\": 412,\n      \"endLine\": 442,\n      \"score\": 0.7937517255544662,\n      \"snippet\": \"- **If you need multiple recipients** (e.g., also send to `luv2worship@gmail.com`), just add that address to `recipient_list` in `copilot-pro.json` or modify the `cfg[\\\"recipient_list\\\"]` array in the script.\\n\\nLet me know once you’ve updated the endpoint/field names and run the script, and we’ll review the result together. If you hit any errors, paste the output here and we’ll refine the call.\\nuser: no output on the test\\nassistant: It looks like the script ran silently. That usually means either:\\n\\n- The script completed without hitting the `print` statements (e.g., it exited early or an exception was swallowed), or\\n- The environment didn’t have the required `MATON_API_KEY` or endpoint, so the\\n\\nSource: memory/2026-03-01-1827.md#L412-L442\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"citation\": \"memory/2026-03-01-1827.md#L412-L442\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \"memory/2026-03-01-1827.md\",\n      \"startLine\": 703,\n      \"endLine\": 722,\n      \"score\": 0.7921895861625671,\n      \"snippet\": \"- Expected: prints SEND_OK with the MATON message and Delivered to: austin.king@parallon.com\\n- If you don’t see output, also try forcing verbose at the top of the script temporarily:\\n  - Add at the very top after imports: print(\\\"DEBUG MATON_API_KEY set?\\\", bool(os.getenv(\\\"MATON_API_KEY\\\")))\\n\\n4) If you get errors, share exact messages\\n- Common failure modes:\\n  - MATON_API_KEY missing or invalid\\n  - Endpoint URL mismatch (need the exact MATON Gmail endpoint from your docs)\\n  - Payload field name mismatch (from/to/subject/text/file)\\n  - Network/timeout issues (check firewall egress)\\n\\n5) Optional: test with a second recipient after initial success\\n- If the corporate test succeeds, you can add a se\\n\\nSource: memory/2026-03-01-1827.md#L703-L722\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"citation\": \"memory/2026-03-01-1827.md#L703-L722\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \"memory/2026-03-01-1827.md\",\n      \"startLine\": 525,\n      \"endLine\": 543,\n      \"score\": 0.7919837653636932,\n      \"snippet\": \"Let me know the results of the debug prints or the minimal test. Once we have a successful API response, the full `generate_daily_report.py` will send the digest as intended.**✅ Quick Summary — What’s happening and next steps**\\n\\n### What we tried\\n- Added a **MATON/Gmail API skeleton** to `generate_daily_report.py`.\\n- Set up the script to:\\n  1. Build a placeholder digest.\\n  2. Write a Markdown attachment.\\n  3. **Send** via the MATON Gmail endpoint (`https://gateway.maton.ai/google‑mail/v1/send`), using `MATON_API_KEY` for auth.\\n- We **ran the script** but got **no output**—meaning it exited before printing the “SEND_OK”/“SEND_FAIL” messages.\\n\\n### Why no output?\\nThe script only prints messages\\n\\nSource: memory/2026-03-01-1827.md#L525-L543\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"citation\": \"memory/2026-03-01-1827.md#L525-L543\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \"memory/2026-03-01-1827.md\",\n      \"startLine\": 363,\n      \"endLine\": 397,\n      \"score\": 0.7908309310674667,\n      \"snippet\": \"if result[\\\"status\\\"] == \\\"ok\\\":\\n        print(\\\"SEND_OK:\\\", result[\\\"message\\\"])\\n        print(\\\"Delivered to:\\\", \\\", \\\".join(recipients))\\n    else:\\n        print(\\\"SEND_FAIL:\\\", result[\\\"message\\\"])\\n        # Exit with non‑zero code so a cron job can notice the failure\\n        raise SystemExit(1)\\n\\nif __name__ == \\\"__main__\\\":\\n    main()\\n```\\n\\n### What you need to adjust for a real send\\n\\n1. **MATON Gmail endpoint**  \\n   Replace `MATON_GMAIL_ENDPOINT` with the exact URL the MATON service exposes for sending Gmail messages (e.g., `https://gateway.maton.ai/google-mail/v1/send` or another version). Check MATON’s API docs for the correct path.\\n\\n2. **Field names**  \\n   Confirm the form‑field names (`from`, `to`\\n\\nSource: memory/2026-03-01-1827.md#L363-L397\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"citation\": \"memory/2026-03-01-1827.md#L363-L397\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"provider\": \"gemini\",\n  \"model\": \"gemini-embedding-001\",\n  \"citations\": \"auto\",\n  \"mode\": \"hybrid\"\n}"}],"details":{"results":[{"path":"memory/2026-03-01-1827.md","startLine":676,"endLine":709,"score":0.8035296112298964,"snippet":"endpoint = \"https://gateway.maton.ai/google-mail/v1/send\"  # update if needed\npayload = {\n  \"from\": \"OpenCopilot Digest <austin.king@parallon.com>\",\n  \"to\": \"austin.king@parallon.com\",\n  \"subject\": \"MATON test email\",\n  \"text\": \"Hello – this is a test from OpenCopilot.\"\n}\nheaders = {\"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {key}\"} if key else {}\nprint(\"Key present:\", bool(key))\nresp = requests.post(endpoint, headers=headers, data=payload, timeout=15)\nprint(\"HTTP status:\", resp.status_code)\ntry:\n  print(\"Response JSON:\", resp.json())\nexcept Exception:\n  print(\"Raw response:\", resp.text[:400])\nPY\n- What to look for:\n  - 200/201 with a useful JSON -> API is reachable and key okay.\n  - 401/403 -> key or scope\n\nSource: memory/2026-03-01-1827.md#L676-L709","source":"memory","citation":"memory/2026-03-01-1827.md#L676-L709"},{"path":"memory/2026-03-01-1827.md","startLine":539,"endLine":582,"score":0.7950693875551224,"snippet":"- The script might have **exited silently** (e.g., `SystemExit` with no print statements) if a required variable was missing.\n\n### What we need to confirm\n1. **`MATON_API_KEY` is actually set** in the environment where the script runs.\n2. **The endpoint URL is correct** (the placeholder may need to be replaced with the real MATON Gmail API endpoint you have access to).\n3. **The request payload format** (field names, `from`, `to`, `subject`, `text`, `file`) matches what the MATON API expects.\n\n### Immediate troubleshooting steps (run them in the same shell)\n\n```bash\n# 1️⃣ Verify the API key is present\necho \"MATON_API_KEY → ${MATON_API_KEY:-<MISSING>}\"\n\n# 2️⃣ Verify the sender email (used in t\n\nSource: memory/2026-03-01-1827.md#L539-L582","source":"memory","citation":"memory/2026-03-01-1827.md#L539-L582"},{"path":"memory/2026-03-01-1827.md","startLine":412,"endLine":442,"score":0.7937517255544662,"snippet":"- **If you need multiple recipients** (e.g., also send to `luv2worship@gmail.com`), just add that address to `recipient_list` in `copilot-pro.json` or modify the `cfg[\"recipient_list\"]` array in the script.\n\nLet me know once you’ve updated the endpoint/field names and run the script, and we’ll review the result together. If you hit any errors, paste the output here and we’ll refine the call.\nuser: no output on the test\nassistant: It looks like the script ran silently. That usually means either:\n\n- The script completed without hitting the `print` statements (e.g., it exited early or an exception was swallowed), or\n- The environment didn’t have the required `MATON_API_KEY` or endpoint, so the\n\nSource: memory/2026-03-01-1827.md#L412-L442","source":"memory","citation":"memory/2026-03-01-1827.md#L412-L442"},{"path":"memory/2026-03-01-1827.md","startLine":703,"endLine":722,"score":0.7921895861625671,"snippet":"- Expected: prints SEND_OK with the MATON message and Delivered to: austin.king@parallon.com\n- If you don’t see output, also try forcing verbose at the top of the script temporarily:\n  - Add at the very top after imports: pr