{"type":"message","id":"18f8a8d2","parentId":"f35ace49","timestamp":"2026-03-02T01:26:54.797Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is referring to \"remembering-conversations-openclaw\" skill. Let me read that skill to understand what it does.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_cb45fc5cc7bb470982b8bcee","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/ec2-user/.openclaw/workspace/skills/remembering-conversations-openclaw/SKILL.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/free","usage":{"input":25047,"output":109,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":25156,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772414811170}}
{"type":"message","id":"fe7775ce","parentId":"18f8a8d2","timestamp":"2026-03-02T01:26:54.809Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_cb45fc5cc7bb470982b8bcee","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: remembering-conversations-openclaw\ndescription: OpenClaw-native conversation memory workflow. Use when the user references prior work/decisions, asks for \"what did we do before\", or when an approach decision benefits from historical context. Uses memory_search/memory_get first, then optional session/subagent history tools.\n---\n\n# Remembering Conversations (OpenClaw Native)\n\n## Core Principle\nSearch before reinventing. Prefer lightweight recall (`memory_search`) over loading long transcripts.\n\n## Workflow\n\n1. **Start with memory tools (mandatory for prior-work questions):**\n   - `memory_search(query)`\n   - `memory_get(path, from, lines)` for top hits\n\n2. **If memory is insufficient, use session tools:**\n   - `sessions_list` to identify likely sessions\n   - `sessions_history(sessionKey, limit)` for targeted review\n\n3. **If synthesis is large, spawn a helper run:**\n   - `sessions_spawn(mode=\"run\", task=\"Summarize prior decisions on X...\")`\n\n4. **Return concise output:**\n   - What was decided\n   - Why\n   - What to do now\n   - Sources/paths when helpful\n\n## When to Use\n- User says: \"last time\", \"before\", \"remember\", \"what did we decide\"\n- You need prior decisions/patterns to avoid duplicate mistakes\n- You’re choosing among approaches and history may contain rationale\n\n## Don’t Use First\n- For current file structure (use read/grep first)\n- For simple one-shot requests without historical context\n\n## Example Queries\n- `memory_search(\"Nashville morning brief schedule decision\")`\n- `memory_search(\"Tessie battery null troubleshooting\")`\n- `memory_search(\"gateway token mismatch fix\")`\n\n## Output Template\n- **Past Decision:** ...\n- **Rationale:** ...\n- **Now Recommended:** ...\n- **Source:** `<path#line>`\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772414814806}}
