{"type":"message","id":"726a63a8","parentId":"80265db9","timestamp":"2026-03-02T01:36:58.169Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"✅ **remembering‑conversations‑openclaw** loaded in this session.  \n\nBased on the last steps I recall:\n\n**Past Decision**  \n- We set up a minimal test using a placeholder `MATON_GMAIL_ENDPOINT` and verified the script structure (no output meant the API key wasn’t set or the endpoint was wrong).  \n\n**Next Steps**  \n1. **Run a quick test** in your shell:  \n\n   ```bash\n   export MATON_API_KEY=\"your_key_here\"\n   python -c \"\"\"\n   import requests, os\n   endpoint = \\\"https://gateway.maton.ai/google-mail/v1/send\\\"\n   payload = {\n       \\\"from\\\": \\\"OpenCopilot Digest <austin.king@parallon.com>\\\",\n       \\\"to\\\": \\\"austin.king@parallon.com\\\",\n       \\\"subject\\\": \\\"MATON test\\\",\n       \\\"text\\\": \\\"Hello – test\\\"\n   }\n   headers = {\\\"Authorization\\\": f\\\"Bearer {os.getenv(\\\"MATON_API_KEY\\\")}\"}\n   print(\\\"Testing: status code =\\\", requests.post(endpoint, headers=headers, json=payload).status_code)\n   \"\"\"\n   ```\n\n   Look for **HTTP 200** or a JSON success response.  \n\n2. **If it works**: the full `generate_daily_report.py` will automatically send your digest to your work email via the Gmail skill.  \n3. **If you hit errors** (401/403, missing key, etc.): paste the exact status and response so I can guide the fix.  \n\nShall I help you edit the script to use iCloud SMTP as the sender instead? Just let me know which approach you’d prefer."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/free","usage":{"input":31640,"output":359,"cacheRead":320,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":32319,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772415400441}}
