{"type":"message","id":"a310c5fe","parentId":"93cfd93e","timestamp":"2026-03-02T03:29:42.101Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here's the corrected script with proper URL quoting:\n\n```bash\npython3 - <<'PY'\nimport os, requests, json\nkey = os.getenv(\"MATON_API_KEY\")\nendpoint = \"https://api.maton.ai/gmail/v1/users/me/messages/send\"  # Ensure quotes here\npayload = {\n    \"from\": \"OpenCopilot Digest <austin.king@parallon.com>\",\n    \"to\": \"austin.king@parallon.com\",\n    \"subject\": \"MATON test\",\n    \"text\": \"Hello – quick test\"\n}\nheaders = {\"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {key}\"} if key else {}\nprint(\"🔧 Sending test request …\")\nresp = requests.post(endpoint, headers=headers, json=payload, timeout=15)\nprint(\"📊 HTTP status:\", resp.status_code)\ntry:\n    print(\"🗂️ JSON response:\", resp.json())\nexcept Exception:\n    print(\"⚠️ Not JSON – raw reply:\", resp.text[:200])\nPY\n```\n\n### To run it:\n\n1. **Copy the entire block above**\n2. **Paste it into your terminal**\n3. **Press Enter**\n\nThis script will:\n- Use your `MATON_API_KEY` environment variable\n- Send a test email via the correct MATON Gmail endpoint\n- Print the HTTP status and response\n\nLet me know what output you get!"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/free","usage":{"input":43273,"output":283,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":43556,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772422161375}}
